# Results — Manhattan Plots

> PNGs are loaded directly from `mp_outdir`. If a run has not been executed yet,
> a placeholder message is shown instead of a missing image error.

```{r plot-helper, include=FALSE}
show_manhattan <- function(run_id) {
  cfg  <- run_config %>% filter(run_id == !!run_id)
  path <- file.path(mp_outdir, paste0(run_id, "_", cfg$Trait, ".png"))
  if (file.exists(path)) {
    knitr::include_graphics(path)
  } else {
    cat("> ⚠️ **Plot not yet generated.**",
        "Run `run_gwas_single(", run_id, ")` in the OPTIONAL block above,",
        "then re-render this document.\n\n")
  }
}
```

